<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Further FEM improvements ===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* Log verbosity and number of threads used for meshing can now be set for [[Image:FEM_MeshGmshFromShape.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MeshGmshFromShape|Gmsh]] and [[Image:FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape|Netgen]] in the [[FEM_Preferences|Preferences]]. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/17699 Pull request #17699] and [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18608 Pull request #18608]
* The {{PropertyData|Second Order Linear}} property and support for [[Image:FEM_MeshRegion.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MeshRegion|local refinement]], previously only available for Gmsh, are now also available for the new [[Image:FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape|Netgen]] implementation. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/17170 Pull request #17170]
* Box and elliptical beam section types were added to [[Image:FEM_ElementGeometry1D.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ElementGeometry1D|FEM ElementGeometry1D]]. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/15843 Pull request #15843]
* The [[Image:FEM_ResultsPurge.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ResultsPurge|Purge results]] tool now deletes all the results objects, not just the ones native to CalculiX. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18328 Pull request #18328]
* [[Image:FEM_ConstraintTie.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintTie|Tie constraint]] can now be applied also to shell faces. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18325 Pull request #18325]
* Output format (binary or ASCII) and saving of geometry IDs can now be set for Elmer, also in [[FEM_Preferences#Elmer|Preferences]]. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/17972 Pull request #17972]
* A smoothing option was added to the [[Image:FEM_PostFilterContours.svg|24px]] [[FEM_PostFilterContours|Contours filter]]. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18088 Pull request #18088]
* The ''BucklingAccuracy'' parameter was added to [[Image:FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools.svg|24px]] [[FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools|CalculiX solver]] - it might be necessary to capture the first eigenvalue in some linear buckling analyses. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18790 Pull request #18790]
* Now all FEM objects for which suppressing makes sense can be suppressed. Previously only constraints were suppressible. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18636 Pull request #18636]
* Contact forces are now printed to ccx_dat_file in CalculiX analyses. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18840 Pull request #18840]
* The [[Image:FEM_MaterialReinforced.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MaterialReinforced|MaterialReinforced]] tool now uses the [[Image:Material_Edit.svg|24px]] [[Material_Edit|new material editor]]. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18893 Pull request #18893]
* The [[Image:FEM_ConstraintElectrostaticPotential.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintElectrostaticPotential|Electrostatic potential boundary condition]] was extended to also support Neumann-type boundary condition and prescribe electric flux density. It now has a symbol too. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18514 Pull request #18514] and [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/19011 Pull request #19011]
* Thermal expansion reference temperature can now be defined for [[Image:FEM_MaterialSolid.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MaterialSolid|solid material]] in thermomechanical analyses with CalculiX. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/19285 Pull request #19285]
* The ''Fem.frdToVTK'' Python function was added allowing conversion of CalculiX's frd results files to VTK format used by ParaView. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/19426 Pull request #19426]
* The [[Image:FEM_ConstraintCurrentDensity.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintCurrentDensity|Current density boundary condition]] was improved. It now has two modes (''Custom'' and ''Normal'') and a symbol for the ''Normal'' mode. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/19930 Pull request #19930]
* Two new [[Image:FEM_Examples.svg|24px]] [[FEM_Examples|FEM examples]] were added - one for the newly implemented [[Image:FEM_EquationStaticCurrent.svg|24px]] [[FEM_EquationStaticCurrent|Static current equation]] (Joule heating) and one for [[Image:FEM_ConstraintRigidBody.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintRigidBody|Rigid body constraint]]. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/20007 Pull request #20007] and [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/20011 Pull request #20011]
* The [[Image:FEM_ConstraintHeatflux.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintHeatflux|Heat flux load]] task panel was improved - radio buttons used to choose the heat flux type were replaced with a combo box. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/20059 Pull request #20059]
* The [[Image:FEM_ConstraintMagnetization.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintMagnetization|Magnetization boundary condition]] task panel was improved. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/20055 Pull request #20055]
* Selection mode was added to Geometry reference selector in the task panels of Elmer equations. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/20053 Pull request #20053]
* The ''renameArrays'' Python function was added to rename selected [[Image:FEM_PostPipelineFromResult.svg|24px]] [[FEM_PostPipelineFromResult|results pipeline]] fields. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/20411 Pull request #20411]
* A [[FEM_Preferences#CalculiX|CalculiX-related preference]] named ''Result object'' was added. If its checkbox ''Pipeline only'' is enabled, a newly refactored CalculiX solver object is added to the Analysis container when using the ''Solver CalculiX'' option. It has an updated task panel, doesn't generate [[Image:FEM_ResultShow.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ResultShow|CCX_Results objects]] (only the [[Image:FEM_PostPipelineFromResult.svg|24px]] [[FEM_PostPipelineFromResult|results pipeline object]] is created) and will be further developed. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/20609 Pull request #20609]
* The ''Offset'' property was added to [[Image:FEM_ElementGeometry2D.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ElementGeometry2D|Shell Plate Thickness]], making it possible to offset the expanded shell from the actual mesh. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22385 Pull request #22385]
* Support for thermal [[Image:FEM_ConstraintContact.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintContact|contact]] with CalculiX was added via ''Enable Thermal Contact'' and ''Thermal Contact Conductance'' properties used to specify gap conductance. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22121 Pull request #22121]
* Support for hard and tied [[Image:FEM_ConstraintContact.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintContact|contact]] with CalculiX was added. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22513 Pull request #22513] and [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23327 Pull request #23327]
* Support for cavity [[Image:FEM_ConstraintHeatflux.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintHeatflux|radiation]] with CalculiX was added. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22593 Pull request #22593]
* Support for amplitudes (time variation) for most mechanical and thermal boundary conditions and loads with CalculiX was added. There are new properties: ''Enable Amplitude'' and ''Amplitude Values''. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22851 Pull request #22851]
* [[Image:FEM_ConstraintInitialTemperature.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintInitialTemperature|Initial temperature]] can now be applied to a selected region (via the ''References'' property) in CalculiX analyses. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22864 Pull request #22864]
* The ''Glue'' property was added to the [[Image:FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape|Netgen mesher]]. When enabled, a continuous mesh is created (this property is equivalent to Gmsh's ''Coherence Mesh''). [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23074 Pull request #23074]
* Default ''Priority'' of Elmer equations now starts with 255 and decreases with each added equation. This way, the equations are solved in the order they were added to the tree. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22999 Pull request #22999]
* CalculiX's membrane and truss elements are now supported and replace shell and beam elements respectively when the new ''ExcludeBendingStiffness'' property of the [[Image:FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools.svg|24px]] [[FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools|CalculiX solver]] is enabled. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22912 Pull request #22912] and [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23224 Pull request #23224]
* Displacements of [[Image:FEM_ConstraintRigidBody.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintRigidBody|rigid body]] reference point are now printed to ccx_dat_file. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23199 Pull request #23199]
* [[Image:FEM_ConstraintInitialTemperature.svg|24px]] [[FEM_ConstraintInitialTemperature|Initial temperature]] can now be also used to prescribe temperature field in a static analysis step (with optional amplitude). [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23277 Pull request #23277] and [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23530 Pull request #23530]
* [[Image:FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape|Netgen]] can now be installed in the standard way mentioned on [https://ngsolve.org/downloads/ its download page] and it is only necessary to point FreeCAD to the proper Python executable in the preferences (by default the Python executable specified in general Python preferences is used). [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23613 Pull request #23613]
* Some preferences related to mesh export now have better defaults. Namely, groups of nodes are enabled for the Gmsh mesher and export to INP files includes FEM elements only and groups by default. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23553 Pull request #23553]
* Properties of the [[Image:FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools.svg|24px]] [[FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools|CalculiX solver]] are now grouped and time incrementation properties are more user-friendly (improved names, better defaults, easy switch between automatic and direct incrementation as well as no need to enable additional property to set non-default incrementation). [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23494 Pull request #23494]
* There is a new ''Pastix Mixed Precision'' property of the [[Image:FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools.svg|24px]] [[FEM_SolverCalculixCcxtools|CalculiX solver]]. It's disabled by default so that mixed precision is not used for the PaStiX matrix solver to avoid issues with incorrect results of some analyses. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23539 Pull request #23539]
* The [[Image:FEM_SolverElmer.svg|24px]] [[FEM_SolverElmer|Elmer solver's]] object and task panel were reworked similar to what was done before for CalculiX. It now works with the new implementation of [[Image:FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape.svg|24px]] [[FEM_MeshNetgenFromShape|Netgen]]. Moreover, ParaView PVD files can now be imported. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/24912 Pull request #24912]
* Three new [[Image:FEM_Examples.svg|24px]] [[FEM_Examples|FEM examples]] were added - one for the newly implemented electrostatics with the refactored CalculiX solver, one for the newly implemented pressure loads on edges of 2D models and one for the cyclic symmetry introduced in FreeCAD 1.0. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/25117 Pull request #25117], [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/25191 Pull request #25191] and [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/25268 Pull request #25268]
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
== Material Workbench ==
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* Materials can now be stored in external datastores. This feature is experimental and has to be activated explicitly when compiling the source code. It is not available in the standard FreeCAD builds. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/21047 Pull request #21047]
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Further Material improvements ===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* Several new materials with physical properties were added to the material database:
