<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
=== Further Part Design improvements ===
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* The origin feature in a Part Design body makes use of the new core datums. The appearance has been changed and the planes enlarge when creating a new sketch. As the orientation was wrong in older FreeCAD versions, files created with these versions need to be converted on opening. It can break files which reference the datums, and converted or new files created with {{VersionPlus|1.1}} will be broken in {{VersionMinus|1.0}}. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18126 Pull request #18126]
* The [[Image:Std_ToggleFreeze.svg|24px]] [[Std_ToggleFreeze|Toggle freeze]] command is now available from Part Design. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/18373 Pull request #18373]
* The performance of modeled threads from the [[Image:PartDesign_Hole.svg|24px]] [[PartDesign_Hole|Hole tool]] has been improved. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/15744 Pull request #15744]
* The initial angle for tapered threads in the [[Image:PartDesign_Hole.svg|24px]] [[PartDesign_Hole|Hole tool]] is now automatically set to the value from the ISO 7-1 and ASME B1.20.1 standards. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/15744 Pull request #15744]
* The [[Image:PartDesign_Hole.svg|24px]] [[PartDesign_Hole|Hole tool]] can now create holes based on sketch points and arcs in addition to circles. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/20583 Pull request #20583]
* ''SwitchToTask'', formerly a  [[Fine-tuning|fine-tuning]] parameter, can now be accessed from the [[PartDesign_Preferences#General|Preferences Editor]]. It can be used to enable and disable automatic switching to the task panel when the Part Design Workbench is activated. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22136 Pull request #22136]
* The [[Image:PartDesign_Pad.svg|24px]] [[PartDesign_Pad|Pad]] task panel was improved to have more options for ''Two sided'' mode. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/21794 Pull request #21794]
* The preference to allow compounds (multiple solids) for Bodies is now enabled by default and not treated as an experimental feature anymore. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/23003 Pull request #23003]
* [[PartDesign_Workbench#Transformation_tools|Transform tools]] can now use different spacing. [https://github.com/FreeCAD/FreeCAD/pull/22389 Pull request #22389]
</div>

